        [
          "A servant of powerful elder society \"the Groundskeepers\" They support the protection of elders and the current power structure. You were a ghoul for well over a century before your Embrace by an elder, but you lack the years as a vampire or true generation to call yoursel one. Your masters have asked you to fake being one to further the Groundskeepers goals.",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Patric Thomas"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You were the ghoul of a powerful Toreador from Scotland, a servant to a secret society of elders called \"The Groundskeepers\" that saw themselves as the cultivators of human and Kindred society. For centuries they have been looking to both guide and prunce the lesser elements of society while also protecting the Elder leadership of the Camarilla. You were a key part of this doing a variety of tasks for your Toreador Elder mistress, willing to do all manner of things to preserve the sanctity of the leadership of the Camarilla to help keep larger Kindred society. Your work earned you the approval of your lady, and as a reward, you were Embraced to keep furthering their work.\n\nYou have been all over the world on the work of the Groundskeepers, and recently you've been asked to go to Los Angeles, a city they've avoided like the plague. It has been a haven for Anarchs, Cathayans and all manner of lesser vampires. But the Camarilla has been trying to establish a long term court there, and Prince Petrovna seems to have succeeded where her predecessors like James Perkins (Queen Anne's childe) and Prince Pictor have failed. They want you in the domain to help press their interests and ensure the Elders power interests in the city. You are asked to go in as an Elder yourself, despite the fact you are no such thing, to start establishing the sort of influence needed and quietly reaching out to those who might be willing to be a part of this group without breaking your cover. Keeping up appearances is important, because should your secret get out, not only do you fail your former mistress and the Groundskeepers, there are those who would kill you for your presumption."
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "Lady Contstance",
          "Reference: (If any)",
          "",
          "",
          "Clan",
          "Toreador \"Ishtarri\" - Presence Sensitivity"
